race.comment: STEEL CLAWS (13) returns after a six-month spell for a fourth campaign. Best efforts are over a bit more ground and he usually needs a run to find form, but with only 55kgs from the inside gate things may fall his way in a modest affair. LUCKY OZZIE (6) appears for the first time since May. Opened the maiden prep with a close fourth over 1000m at Tamworth but faltered after that. Probably improved over the break and is capable of testing this field. MISS HEROIC (12) led and just failed to hang on last time out over this trip at Moree when lining up for the 18th time. Running out of chances but that last effort was encouraging. TIPSY MISS (7) made late inroads but was never a winning chance on debut over 1000m at Scone last start. Sure to appreciate an extra furlong today. EFFIETRINKET (5) produced a career-best performance at Moree last time out and at the third run back still has plenty to offer.
